  "prompt": "How do I know what he feels about me?",
  "response": "Okay, trying to figure out someone's feelings is a classic human dilemma! Unfortunately, there's no magic formula, but here's a breakdown of things to look for, consider, and how to approach the situation:\n\n**1. Observe His Behavior (Actions Speak Louder Than Words - Sometimes!)**\n\n*   **How does he act around you compared to others?**\n    *   Does he seem more attentive, nervous, or playful?\n    *   Does he single you out for conversation or attention?\n    *   Does he seem to mirror your body language (subconsciously copying your gestures or posture)?\n*   **Initiation and Engagement:**\n    *   **Does he initiate contact?**  Texts, calls, DMs, or finding excuses to talk in person are good signs.  How often does he do this?\n    *   **How engaged is he when you're talking?**  Does he maintain eye contact, ask follow-up questions, and actively listen?\n    *   **Does he remember details you've told him?**  This shows he's paying attention and cares about what you say.\n*   **Physical Touch (Context Matters!)**\n    *   **Does he find excuses to touch you?** A light touch on the arm, a playful nudge, or lingering hugs can be indicators, but consider the context.  Is he generally touchy-feely with everyone, or is it reserved for you?  (Be mindful of boundaries and your own comfort level!)\n    *   **Body Language:** Does he lean in when you talk? Does he angle his body towards you? Does he maintain eye contact?\n*   **Effort and Time:**\n    *   **Does he make an effort to spend time with you?**  Does he go out of his way to help you, even with small things?\n    *   **Does he prioritize you in his schedule?**  If he's busy but still makes time for you, it's a positive sign.\n*   **Jealousy (Handle with Caution!)**\n    *   **Does he seem bothered when you talk about other guys?**  A little jealousy can be a sign of interest, but excessive jealousy is a red flag and indicates insecurity and potential control issues.\n*   **Humor and Teasing:**\n    *   **Does he tease you playfully?**  Teasing can be a way of flirting and testing the waters.\n    *   **Does he laugh at your jokes, even the not-so-funny ones?**\n\n**2. Listen to His Words (But Don't Take Everything at Face Value)**\n\n*   **Compliments:** Does he compliment you on things other than just your appearance? Does he praise your intelligence, humor, or kindness?\n*   **\"We\" Language:** Does he use \"we\" or \"us\" when talking about future plans or shared experiences? This suggests he's thinking of you as a unit.\n*   **Vulnerability:** Does he open up to you about his feelings, thoughts, and experiences? Sharing personal information is a sign of trust and intimacy.\n*   **Direct Statements:** Has he explicitly said he likes you, cares about you, or has feelings for you?  This is the most obvious, but some people are afraid to be so direct.\n*   **Be wary of flattery:** Sometimes, excessive flattery can be a sign of manipulation. Look for genuine compliments that reflect your personality and character.\n\n**3. Consider the Context and Your Relationship**\n\n*   **How long have you known him?**  Feelings take time to develop.\n*   **What's the nature of your relationship?** Are you friends, coworkers, classmates, or something else? This will influence the types of interactions you have.\n*   **His personality:** Is he naturally shy or outgoing?  Is he generally expressive or reserved?  This will affect how he shows his feelings.\n*   **His past experiences:** Has he been hurt in the past? This might make him more cautious about expressing his feelings.\n*   **Cultural background:** Cultural norms can influence how people express their emotions.\n\n**4. Trust Your Gut**\n\n*   **What does your intuition tell you?**  Sometimes, you just have a feeling.  Don't ignore your gut, but also don't rely on it exclusively.\n*   **Are you hoping to see signs that aren't really there?** Be honest with yourself about whether you're projecting your own feelings onto him.\n\n**5. The Most Direct Approach: Communicate!**\n\n*   **Talk to him!**  This is the most reliable way to find out how he feels.\n    *   **Start with a casual conversation:** \"I've really enjoyed spending time with you lately.  I was wondering how you feel about our relationship?\"\n    *   **Be open and honest about your own feelings:**  \"I've developed feelings for you, and I wanted to know if you feel the same way.\"\n    *   **Be prepared for any answer:** He might reciprocate your feelings, he might not, or he might need time to think about it.\n    *   **Respect his answer:** Even if it's not what you wanted to hear, respect his honesty and move on.\n*   **Frame it as a question of understanding:** \"I'm getting mixed signals, and I just want to make sure I'm understanding things correctly. How do you see our relationship?\"\n*   **Choose the right time and place:**  Pick a time when you're both relaxed and can talk openly and honestly without distractions.\n*   **Don't put him on the spot in front of others.**\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Respect Boundaries:**  Don't pressure him to reveal his feelings if he's not ready.\n*   **Don't Play Games:** Be genuine and avoid manipulative tactics.\n*   **Be Patient:**  It takes time for feelings to develop and for people to feel comfortable expressing them.\n*   **Focus on Building a Connection:**  Regardless of whether he has romantic feelings for you, focus on building a strong and meaningful connection.\n\n**In summary, look for a combination of consistent actions, genuine words, and trust your intuition. But the most reliable way to know for sure is to have an open and honest conversation with him.** Good luck!\n",
